Creating React 18x Applicattion
- React application can be built by using various bundling tools.
    a. Webpack
    b. Parcel
    c. Vite

- Bundling tools allow to configure a complete web application for enviroments like 
    a. Development
    b. Quality [Testing]
    c. Production

- Node JS provides support for Webpack bundler, hene you can create a react application by using Webpack bundler if Node JS installed on your PC.

- Create project by using the following command
    > npx create-react-app app-name

- Open Project folder in VS Code

- React Application File system comprises of the following

    File / Folder                    Description
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    public                           contians static resources like html, images, docs, etc.
    src                              contains dynamic resources like scss, css, js, jsx, ts, tsx, etc.
    node_modules                     contains all library file installed using NPM package manager.
    package.json                     contains project meta data.
    package.lock.json                contains complete dependencies list are used for project.
    .gitignore                       cofigures the resources to ignore while publishing on to GIT.
    README.md                        conatains help documentation.

